## üéØ How to Use This Documentation

### If You're **NEW** to the Project:
```
1. Read VISUAL_QUICK_START.md (10 min)
   ‚Üì
2. Look at REQUEST_FLOW_DIAGRAMS.md ‚Üí "Overall System Architecture" (3 min)
   ‚Üì
3. Read EXECUTIVE_SUMMARY.md (10 min)
   ‚Üì
4. Run the application locally
   ‚Üì
5. Test an API endpoint
   ‚Üì
6. Then read BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE_DOCUMENTATION.md for depth
```

### If You're **DEVELOPING** a Feature:
```
1. Consult QUICK_REFERENCE.md for existing endpoints (2 min)
   ‚Üì
2. Find similar flow in REQUEST_FLOW_DIAGRAMS.md (5 min)
   ‚Üì
3. Reference BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE_DOCUMENTATION.md for patterns (10 min)
   ‚Üì
4. Code your feature
   ‚Üì
5. Test with curl or Postman
```

### If You're **DEBUGGING** an Issue:
```
1. Identify the API endpoint in QUICK_REFERENCE.md (1 min)
   ‚Üì
2. Find the flow in REQUEST_FLOW_DIAGRAMS.md (5 min)
   ‚Üì
3. Check error scenarios in REQUEST_FLOW_DIAGRAMS.md ‚Üí "Error Handling Flow" (3 min)
   ‚Üì
4. Look up detailed logic in BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE_DOCUMENTATION.md (10 min)
   ‚Üì
5. Debug your issue
```

### If You're in an **INTERVIEW**:
```
1. Study BACKEND_ARCHITECTURE_DOCUMENTATION.md thoroughly
   ‚Üì
2. Practice explaining flows from REQUEST_FLOW_DIAGRAMS.md
   ‚Üì
3. Keep QUICK_REFERENCE.md nearby for specific details
   ‚Üì
4. Reference EXECUTIVE_SUMMARY.md for talking points
   ‚Üì
5. Be ready to explain any part of the system
```

